did.unittitle: Dawn Eichenlaub historic preservation research collection
did.abstract: This collection contains the research files of Dawn Eichenlaub. The type of document include legal cases, brochures, meeting agendas, reports, organizational charts, newsletters, and newspaper articles. These materials date from 1965-1983 with the bulk falling between 1976-1978. The subjects relate to historic preservation primarily within the D.C. metropolitan area and are mostly for different historic preservation organizations working in the city. These organizations include both federal agencies and non-profits.
did.physloc: Materials may be stored off-site, and may require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

bioghist.head: Biography
bioghist.p: Dawn Eichenlaub was a 1983 graduate of GW. Her masters thesis is titled Rhodes Tavern and Square 224: 1978-1983 A Case Study of Preservation Practices in Washington, D.C.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The folders within this collection are maintained in the order in which they were donated. The folders appear to have a semblance of alphabetical order by folder title through most of box 3, but the order is only loosely in alphabetical order for half of box 3, box 4 and box 5.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains the research files of Dawn Eichenlaub. The type of document include legal cases, brochures, meeting agendas, reports, organizational charts, publications, newsletters, and newspaper articles. These materials date from 1965-1983 with the bulk falling between 1976-1978. The subjects relate to historic preservation primarily within the D.C. metropolitan area and are mostly for different historic preservation organizations working in the city. These organizations include both federal agencies and non-profits.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.
